# Git commits

When creating commits in this repository:

- **Author:** `Jas0n0ss <Jas0n0ss@hotmail.com>`
- **Never** commit as `cursoragent`, `Cursor Agent`, or any Cursor default identity.
- Use explicit author on every commit:

```bash
git commit --author="Jas0n0ss <Jas0n0ss@hotmail.com>" -m "$(cat <<'EOF'
message here
EOF
)"
```

- Do **not** run `git config` to change user.name/user.email (user manages that locally).
- Before pushing, verify: `git log -1 --format='%an <%ae>'` must show Jas0n0ss.
